.TH "SYMBOL.DISPOSE" "3JS" "August 2, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Symbol.dispose \- Symbol.dispose
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Symbol.dispose\f[B]\f[R] static data property represents
the well\-known symbol \f[CR]Symbol.dispose\f[R].
The \f[CR]using\f[R] declaration looks up this symbol on the variable
initializer for the method to call when the variable goes out of scope.
.SH VALUE
The well\-known symbol \f[CR]Symbol.dispose\f[R].
.PP
.TS
tab(@);
